9 SECTION 5. ORS 682.500 is amended to read:
10 682.500. (1) The Emergency Medical Services Program is established within the Oregon Health
11 Authority for the purpose of administering a comprehensive statewide emergency medical services
12 system developed by the Emergency Medical Services Advisory Board and focused on emergency
13 medical services and time-sensitive emergencies. The system includes:
14 (a) The development of state and regional standards of emergency medical care;
15 (b) The development of state, regional and interstate protocols for patient transfers using
16 emergency medical services;
17 (c) The training and licensing of emergency medical services providers;
18 (d) The development and management of emergency medical services data systems;
19 (e) The management and administration of state workforce, recruitment and retention programs
20 related to emergency medical services; and
21 [(f) The regulation and administration of state reimbursement systems for emergency medical ser-
22 vices; and]
23 [(g)] (f) Requirements for reporting out measurable performance and equity indicators of emer-
24 gency medical services within this state.
25 (2) The program is administered by a director who:
26 (a) Is responsible for conducting emergency medical services system oversight and implementing
27 the recommendations of the advisory board.
28 (b) Shall apply funds allocated to the program in the following order of priority:
29 (A) Development of state and regional standards of care;
30 (B) Strengthening the state’s emergency medical services workforce;
31 (C) Development of statewide educational curriculum to teach the standards of care;
32 (D) Implementation of quality improvement programs; and
33 (E) Support for and enhancement of the state’s emergency medical services.
34 (c) May adopt rules as necessary to carry out the director’s duties and responsibilities described
35 in this subsection.
36 (3) The program shall have a State EMS Medical Director who is the chairperson of the Emer-
37 gency Medical Services Advisory Board established under ORS 682.506 and who is responsible for:
38 (a) Providing specialized medical oversight in the development and administration of the pro-
39 gram;
40 (b) Implementing emergency medical services quality improvement measures;
41 (c) Undertaking research and providing public education regarding emergency medical services;
42 and
43 (d) Serving as a liaison with emergency medical services agencies, emergency medical services
44 centers, hospitals, state and national emergency medical services professional organizations and
45 state and federal partners.
