35 ambulance unless [it] the ambulance is operated with at least one emergency medical services
36 provider who is licensed at a level higher than emergency medical responder.
37 (4) It is a defense to any charge under this section that there was a reasonable basis for be-
38 lieving that the performance of services contrary to this section was necessary to preserve human
39 life, that diligent effort was made to obtain the services of a licensed emergency medical services
40 provider and that the services of a licensed emergency medical services provider were not available
41 or were not available in time as under the circumstances appeared necessary to preserve such hu-
42 man life.
